  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "However, we argue that the fact that people often perceive it to be conscious is important and has social consequences.",
    "Mind perception is central to this process, and mind perception itself evokes moral thinking.",
    "Some researchers claim that \"mind perception is the essence of morality\" (Gray and Wegner, 2012).",
    "When people perceive mind in an agent, they may also view it as capable of having conscious experience and therefore perceive it as something worthy of moral care (Gray et al., 2007).",
    "Mind perception moderates whether someone judges an artificial agent's actions as moral or immoral (Shank et al., 2021)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
